description: Describes a predefined attribute for the specified Amazon Connect instance. Predefined attributes are attributes in an Amazon Connect instance that can be used to route contacts to an agent or pools of agents within a queue. For more information, see Create predefined attributes for routing contacts to agents.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instance ID in the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the instance.

parameters.name: Name
parameters.description: The name of the predefined attribute.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the predefined attribute.

nested_items.name: StringList
nested_items.description: Predefined attribute values of type string list.
